@startuml deployment-diagram
title FitFood — Deployment View

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #FDFDFD
}

actor "Customer\n(web browser)" as User

node "VPS / Docker host" as Host {

  node "app container\n(Dockerfile)" as AppNode {
    artifact "FastAPI (uvicorn)\nlistens :8000" as Api
    artifact "Next.js static export\n(frontend/out)\nserved by StaticFiles" as Static
  }

  node "db container\n(postgres:16-alpine)" as DbNode {
    database "PostgreSQL" as PG
  }

  folder "named volume\npgdata" as Vol
}

cloud "LLM provider\n(OpenRouter / OpenAI / Ollama)" as LLM
cloud "FNS receipt API\n(proverkacheka.com)" as FNS

User --> Api : HTTPS :8000\n(API + SPA, same origin)
Api ..> Static : serve UI
Api --> PG : SQLAlchemy\n(DATABASE_URL)
PG --> Vol : persist data
Api ..> LLM : outbound HTTPS\n(key from env; mock if unset)
Api ..> FNS : outbound HTTPS\n(token from env; mock if unset)

note bottom of Host
  docker compose up --build
  * default dev run uses embedded SQLite (no db container)
  * compose profile swaps in PostgreSQL via DATABASE_URL
  * secrets (SECRET_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, CHECK_TOKEN)
    injected as env vars, never baked into the image
end note

@enduml
